&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Speech and Language Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to work 37.5 hours per week as a band 6 SLT with a specialism/developing specialism in complex communication needs and AAC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is based across the primary site of a Haringey special school, working with students aged 4-11 with a range of special needs including cerebral palsy, ASD and PMLD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our SLT team is well established alongside the multi-disciplinary team within the school. You will have support from highly specialist AAC and dysphagia colleagues as well as supporting junior team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLaura HillsEmail addresslaura.hills@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details please contact Laura Hills Lead speech and Language Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;laura.hills@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
